chapter.p:
Thank you, William;
                    you were always good to me, said the young man gratefully. This is delightful, and he stretched his numbed
                hands over the blazing wood, and looked round the room with a satisfied smile.

No, sir, I have found them, was the answer;
                    and I mean to strive and make a better thing of my life than I should ever
                    have done had I not gone to the Old House in Vauxhall Walk.
